\section{Review of Exponentials}

You should know all the following formulas:

\begin{thm} \mbox{}
\begin{itemize}
\item[(a)] If $b \neq 0$, then $b^0 = 1$.
\item[(b)] $b^x \cdot b^y = b^{x + y}$
\item[(c)] $(b^x)^y = b^{xy}$
\item[(d)] $b^{-x} = \frac{1}{b^x}$
\end{itemize}
\end{thm}

Note that 
\[
0^0
\]
is undefined. 
[This is a very good question for your math instructor.]
